history.content:
There is a miscompilation issue report in InstCombine: 

Clang at -O1 and above produces the wrong code.

Bisected to e4710872e98a931c6d5e89bc965b778746ead2c0, which was committed by @nikic 

Compiler explorer: https://godbolt.org/z/n4Kj5WPKe

```console
% cat a.c
int printf(const char *, ...);
int a;
short b, c = 1;
short *e = &b;
char f;
int main() {
  int g = c, h = -1, i = -1, d = 8;
  g |= 0 || i;
  if (d)
    a = 2;
  *e = f ^ a + h + i + g + h;
  printf("%d\n", b);
}
%
% clang -O0 a.c && ./a.out
0
% clang -O1 a.c && ./a.out
1
%
```

The maintainers proposed the following patch to fix the issue:

commit 09a05f5dcb7946494828b00d767198341ff78604
Author: Craig Topper <craig.topper@sifive.com>
Date:   Thu Dec 7 13:03:53 2023 -0800

    [InstCombine] Drop poison generating flags on Or in simplifyAssocCastAssoc.

    Fixes #74739.

diff --git a/llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstructionCombining.cpp b/llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstructionCombining.cpp
index 30e058000d2b..f072f5cec309 100644
--- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstructionCombining.cpp
+++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstructionCombining.cpp
@@ -356,6 +356,7 @@ static bool simplifyAssocCastAssoc(BinaryOperator *BinOp1,

   IC.replaceOperand(*Cast, 0, BinOp2->getOperand(0));
   IC.replaceOperand(*BinOp1, 1, FoldedC);
+  BinOp1->dropPoisonGeneratingFlags();
   Cast->dropPoisonGeneratingFlags();
   return true;
 }


